# CODEOWNERS — require review from owning team on changes to their modules
# Syntax: <path pattern>  <@user or @org/team>
# Replace team handles with your actual GitHub org/team slugs.

# Core systems & DI setup — Platform team must review
/Assets/_Game/Core/                         @your-org/platform-team
/Assets/_Game/GamePlay/                     @your-org/platform-team
/Assets/_Game/Core/VContainer/              @your-org/platform-team

# Gameplay features — Gameplay team must review
/Assets/_Game/Features/Player/              @your-org/gameplay-team
/Assets/_Game/Features/Asteroids/          @your-org/gameplay-team
/Assets/_Game/Features/Waves/              @your-org/gameplay-team
/Assets/_Game/Features/Weapons/            @your-org/gameplay-team
/Assets/_Game/Features/ScreenWrap/         @your-org/gameplay-team

# UI — UI team must review
/Assets/_Game/UI/                           @your-org/ui-team

# Tests — owning team + QA must both review
/Assets/_Game/Tests/                        @your-org/gameplay-team @your-org/qa-team
/Assets/_Game/Core/Tests/                   @your-org/platform-team @your-org/qa-team

# Package manifest — any dependency change needs tech lead sign-off
/Packages/manifest.json                     @your-org/platform-team @your-org/tech-leads
/ThirdPartyPackages/                        @your-org/platform-team @your-org/tech-leads

# Architecture docs — tech leads review
/docs/                                      @your-org/tech-leads
/ARCHITECTURE_AUDIT.md                      @your-org/tech-leads
